# Codexify Source Available License v0.1 (Draft)

Copyright (c) 2025 Resonant Constructs LLC and the Codexify contributors, if
any. All rights reserved.

## 1. Preamble

Codexify is being shared as source-available software so that people can inspect
the code, learn from it, audit it, and run it locally for limited free-use
purposes.

This license is not an OSI-approved open source license and must not be
described as "open source" in the strict legal sense unless the project owner
later replaces this license with an OSI-approved license.

This draft is intended to express the project owner's current release posture:
local-first beta software, visible source, narrow proof-driven claims, and no
unrestricted commercial exploitation.

## 2. Definitions

"Licensor" means Resonant Constructs LLC or the project owner that publishes
Codexify under this license.

"Software" means the Codexify source code, documentation, build scripts,
configuration, and other materials distributed with this repository, excluding
third-party components distributed under their own terms.

"You" means the individual or legal entity exercising rights under this
license.

"Free Use" means personal, educational, hobbyist, research, evaluation, and
local or private non-commercial use by an individual or a small private group
where the Software is not used to generate revenue, support paid delivery, or
operate production infrastructure for an organization.

"Commercial Use" means any use of the Software that is connected to revenue,
paid services, client work, internal company operations, organizational
production systems, customer-facing delivery, or other business activity.

"Hosted Service" means making the Software available to third parties over a
network, including as a hosted application, API, managed service, shared
instance, or software-as-a-service offering.

"Marks" means the Codexify name, product names, logos, trade dress, branding,
and other source-identifying terms or assets associated with the Software.

## 3. Permitted Free Uses

Subject to this license, You may for Free Use only:

1. view, download, and run the Software;
2. study, audit, benchmark, and evaluate the Software;
3. modify the Software for Your own Free Use;
4. share non-production forks or patches for discussion, learning, review, or
   contribution, provided that You keep this license notice and do not imply
   project-owner endorsement.

The permitted free-use boundary is intended to allow local, private,
non-commercial use, including personal experimentation and research, without
granting unrestricted deployment rights.

## 4. Commercial Use Requires a Separate Paid License

You may not engage in Commercial Use of the Software unless You first obtain a
separate written commercial license from the Licensor.

Commercial Use requiring a separate paid license includes, without limitation:

1. company or organizational production use;
2. use as operational infrastructure for paid work or client delivery;
3. customer-facing deployments;
4. paid support, managed-service, or consulting offerings built on the
   Software;
5. embedding the Software into a paid product, subscription, or service;
6. white-label, OEM, sublicensed, or resale distribution.

## 5. SaaS / Hosted Service Restriction

You may not use the Software to operate, power, expose, or support a Hosted
Service for third parties without a separate written commercial license.

This restriction applies whether the Hosted Service is public, private,
customer-specific, internal to an organization, or otherwise accessible over a
network for operational use beyond Free Use.

## 6. Redistribution and Forks

You may redistribute the unmodified Software or modified forks only for Free
Use, review, education, research, or contribution-oriented purposes, and only
if:

1. this license and all copyright notices are preserved;
2. recipients are informed that the Software is source-available, not OSI open
   source;
3. no Commercial Use rights are granted or implied;
4. Your fork does not use the Marks or present itself as an official Codexify
   release.

Redistribution for sale, paid access, managed hosting, commercial support, or
other Commercial Use requires a separate written commercial license.

## 7. No Trademark License

No trademark, trade name, logo, branding, or other Marks license is granted by
this document.

You may not use the Marks in connection with forks, derivative works,
deployments, marketing, domain names, package names, service names, or product
identity language without prior written permission from the Licensor.

